Testing the Route

With the route created you're now ready to test it out. The easiest way to make sure everything is working is by sending a Note using the Notecard's in-browser terminal.

Use the in-browser terminal to connect to your Notecard via USB. (If you're unsure how to do this check out the Notecard quickstart.)

Once connected, associate your Notecard with a Notehub project (if it isn't already).

COPY
{
  "req": "hub.set",
  "product": "com.example.yourname:yourproject"
}

Next, run the command below to queue a Note onto the data.qo Notefile. You may wish to change the file and body of your command, depending on how you configured your route.

COPY
{
  "req": "note.add",
  "file": "data.qo",
  "body": {
    "temp": 22
  }
}

Finally, run the hub.sync request to send this data to your Notehub project.

COPY
{
  "req": "hub.sync"
}

When the data reaches your Notehub project, Notehub will automatically route your sensor data to Slack. And if all goes well, you should see your message appear in your channel. For example, if you use a Text of [.body], you should see a message that looks like this.

